WEBVTT

00:02.333 --> 00:03.589
<i>Previously on "Nashville"...</i>

00:03.753 --> 00:05.893
Rayna, I want you to meet Juliette Barnes.

00:06.134 --> 00:07.713
An arena tour with Juliette.

00:07.884 --> 00:09.625
I cannot believe we have to do this.

00:09.926 --> 00:11.923
(Bucky) Scarlett, you just got
yourself a record deal. (Screams)

00:12.890 --> 00:15.271
Now you're moving in with my
woman? You didn't deserve her.

00:15.462 --> 00:16.678
Will you marry me?

00:16.929 --> 00:18.766
I love you. That is the truth.

00:20.041 --> 00:21.417
I'm pregnant.

00:21.887 --> 00:24.024
You're demoting me? I quit.

00:25.448 --> 00:26.724
Go. Just get out.

00:26.872 --> 00:28.409
(Juliette) My mother is a drug addict.

00:28.565 --> 00:30.459
Mama? No! (Sobbing)

00:30.624 --> 00:32.360
(Voice breaks) I think
that you might be my father.

00:32.610 --> 00:34.309
Stop it. (Shouts indistinctly)

00:34.491 --> 00:35.267
(Tires screech)

00:35.398 --> 00:36.945
(Engine hissing, metal creaking)

00:40.661 --> 00:42.789
(Liquid dripping)

00:44.375 --> 00:45.409
(Grunting)

00:49.021 --> 00:50.229
Rayna... Rayna?

00:50.845 --> 00:52.304
Baby? Baby, wake up. (Car door opens)

00:53.010 --> 00:53.891
(Breathing heavily)

00:55.050 --> 00:57.931
Hold on. (groaning)

01:02.646 --> 01:04.163
(Thud)

01:05.515 --> 01:06.429
Come on, babe.

01:06.599 --> 01:08.206
Baby, wake up. You gotta wake up.

01:09.404 --> 01:11.422
Aah! (Grunting)

01:12.480 --> 01:15.071
(Siren wailing in distance)

01:15.265 --> 01:16.578
Aah!

01:16.953 --> 01:19.724
(Panting)

01:22.423 --> 01:24.366
(Rayna) What are we doing here?

01:24.606 --> 01:25.888
Oh, my gosh.

01:26.061 --> 01:27.633
All right, we're gonna
have to do this fast,

01:27.791 --> 01:29.467
'cause I gotta get to my C.M.A. Rehearsal.

01:29.617 --> 01:30.781
(Deacon) Well, what's more important,

01:30.951 --> 01:32.331
me or a C.M.A. Rehearsal?

01:32.503 --> 01:33.796
Well, it's not a competition,

01:33.977 --> 01:36.522
- but it is my first nomination, so...
- Yeah, well, it's not gonna be your last.

01:36.814 --> 01:38.060
All right, come on.

01:40.194 --> 01:41.536
(Gasps)

01:41.766 --> 01:43.510
Now look, I know when you're
a big country superstar,

01:43.703 --> 01:45.241
this might not seem
like much, but for now...

01:45.410 --> 01:46.911
It's my dream house.

01:47.143 --> 01:48.568
There's still about 300 payments left

01:48.722 --> 01:50.081
on your dream house, but, uh...

01:50.237 --> 01:52.569
- You're not supposed to make big decisions.
- After rehab, I know.

01:53.000 --> 01:54.972
But you weren't supposed to
have to take my drunk ass there

01:55.145 --> 01:57.174
in the first place, so... Mmm.

01:58.229 --> 01:59.450
(Whispers) Thank you...

02:00.353 --> 02:01.595
For loving me more than I deserve.

02:01.861 --> 02:03.248
I know.

02:04.407 --> 02:06.500
You happy?

02:06.721 --> 02:08.585
Yeah, I'm happy. (Chuckles)

02:09.396 --> 02:10.359
What's the matter?

02:10.695 --> 02:11.760
(Exhales)

02:11.908 --> 02:13.616
You're just so damn beautiful.

02:14.348 --> 02:19.663
(Monitor beeping steadily,
ventilator whooshing)

02:19.845 --> 02:21.687
(Daphne) How much longer
does she have to stay asleep?

02:21.871 --> 02:23.105
(Maddie) She's not sleeping.

02:23.289 --> 02:26.307
She's in a coma... One they put her in.

02:27.007 --> 02:28.730
The doctors keep her this
way because they're worried

02:28.905 --> 02:30.388
about brain damage, too.

02:30.562 --> 02:33.371
Sometimes a person's brain
can get a little swollen.

02:33.858 --> 02:35.592
That could be really dangerous.

02:36.255 --> 02:38.338
But the doctors... they're...
they're watching her,

02:39.113 --> 02:40.917
and they're checking on her all the time.

02:41.120 --> 02:43.032
But it's already been two weeks.

02:43.441 --> 02:44.659
I know, baby.

02:47.704 --> 02:49.223
All right, you two.

02:49.403 --> 02:50.709
Can I stay with her today?

02:50.880 --> 02:52.213
I wanna stay, too.

02:53.314 --> 02:54.659
I'll check with your father.

02:55.983 --> 02:57.328
(Man) Deacon Claybourne.

02:58.121 --> 02:58.874
Yes, your honor?

02:59.054 --> 03:00.027
Mr. Claybourne, you're being charged with

03:00.174 --> 03:02.201
driving under the influence
and reckless driving.

03:02.581 --> 03:04.119
Now did you receive adequate medical care

03:04.281 --> 03:06.994
- while you were in the hospital jail ward?
- Yes, your honor.

03:07.466 --> 03:08.560
(Lowered voice) If he thinks
he's getting out of there

03:08.745 --> 03:09.995
while my wife fights for her life,

03:10.214 --> 03:11.093
- he better think again.
- Ex.

03:11.645 --> 03:13.305
Just tell me you made my
position clear to the judge.

03:13.574 --> 03:14.782
I did.

03:15.005 --> 03:16.109
Helps that you're the mayor.

03:16.322 --> 03:17.513
Sir, given your past criminal record,

03:17.750 --> 03:20.065
and given the danger you appear
to pose to yourself and to others,

03:21.179 --> 03:23.744
I'm setting the bail at $1 million.

03:24.387 --> 03:26.047
(Gallery murmuring)

03:26.714 --> 03:28.199
Now you have the right to an attorney,

03:28.399 --> 03:29.521
and one will be appointed
for you should you...

03:29.643 --> 03:30.885
Don't want one.

03:31.193 --> 03:33.267
Does this mean you intend
to represent yourself?

03:33.472 --> 03:34.866
Just ready to plead guilty.

03:35.040 --> 03:38.275
Mr. Claybourne, your passenger
remains in critical condition,

03:38.589 --> 03:40.019
and if she does not survive,

03:40.377 --> 03:42.144
these charges are going to be upgraded

03:42.482 --> 03:44.188
to involuntary manslaughter.

03:44.501 --> 03:46.032
Say "yes" to a lawyer.

03:46.569 --> 03:48.101
(Gavel bangs) Next case.

03:48.398 --> 03:49.471
Let's go.

03:55.588 --> 03:57.849
<i>(Woman on TV) Seen by many as the
reigning queen of country music,</i>

03:58.029 --> 03:59.944
<i>Rayna's storied career has won fans</i>

04:00.151 --> 04:03.092
<i>all across the globe,
and although hospitalized,</i>

04:03.293 --> 04:05.148
<i>she continues to do so.</i>

04:05.343 --> 04:07.055
Okay. Personal assistant candidate

04:07.221 --> 04:08.491
should be here any minute.

04:09.089 --> 04:10.148
<i>Accident that's left her clinging to life,</i>

04:10.350 --> 04:11.495
<i>it's clear this queen</i>

04:11.724 --> 04:13.394
<i>is staying at the top of the charts.</i>

04:13.669 --> 04:15.283
<i>Fans continue to visit the...</i>

04:15.528 --> 04:16.851
- Hey, you all right?
- My album drops tomorrow.

04:17.134 --> 04:18.314
If she's holding on to number one,

04:18.572 --> 04:19.755
you know what that means for me?

04:19.934 --> 04:21.892
It's hard enough to bust
out of this tween demo.

04:22.077 --> 04:23.823
Now I have to compete
with a Saint in a coma.

04:24.110 --> 04:25.763
(TV turns off, remote control
clatters) Juliette, look, it doesn't...

04:25.903 --> 04:27.365
I want the release date pushed.

04:27.582 --> 04:29.361
Call Marshall. Tell him we
need to set up a meeting...

04:29.508 --> 04:30.806
Marshall's not the decision maker anymore.

04:30.995 --> 04:32.245
Well, then tell whoever's in charge.

04:32.425 --> 04:34.406
The label's just been sucked
into this massive conglomerate.

04:34.586 --> 04:36.032
Now trust me. Their board of directors

04:36.248 --> 04:38.336
does not give a damn
about Edgehill Records,

04:38.946 --> 04:40.224
and until they name a new president,

04:40.539 --> 04:42.178
there's nobody there for me or you

04:42.576 --> 04:44.737
to yell at. (Doorbell rings)
I mean, if it were up to me,

04:44.979 --> 04:47.156
you wouldn't do an album
launch concert tomorrow.

04:47.445 --> 04:48.824
You just lost your mom.

04:49.030 --> 04:50.509
(Door opens) Now this
thing with Rayna, you know?

04:50.682 --> 04:51.896
Sweetie, look, you need a break.

04:52.125 --> 04:54.166
- You need...
- A break is last thing that I need, Glenn.

04:54.335 --> 04:55.820
(Door closes) (Bo) Right this way.

04:56.242 --> 04:57.471
(Man) I'm here for the job interview?

04:57.719 --> 04:59.416
(Sighs) Tell me you're an orphan,

04:59.617 --> 05:00.801
because the woman you'd be replacing

05:01.045 --> 05:03.556
has a sick relative, which has
been very inconvenient for me.

05:03.772 --> 05:06.155
I'm an only child, and
both folks have passed.

05:06.394 --> 05:08.725
I'm... sorry that she
left you in the lurch.

05:10.120 --> 05:11.894
I was just walking my manager out.

05:14.777 --> 05:15.870
(Lowered voice) I can handle this.

05:17.647 --> 05:18.648
You deal with Edgehill.

05:18.856 --> 05:21.399
There is no way I'm letting old
Rayna Jaymes songs tank my record.

05:21.700 --> 05:23.885
(Lowered voice) Is that what you're
really the most concerned about right now?

05:27.036 --> 05:30.347
(Scarlett, lowered voice) It's my
last night, so don't tell anybody.

05:31.003 --> 05:32.349
This is on the house.

05:32.082 --> 05:34.310
<i>(Lord Huron) ♪ I will be back one day</i>

05:34.529 --> 05:37.805
<i>♪ and I'll find you there
by the great big lake ♪</i>

05:37.979 --> 05:39.096
Zoey.

05:39.495 --> 05:40.594
<i>Zoey.</i>

05:41.231 --> 05:43.748
You gotta make sure the
singer has a drink first,

05:43.965 --> 05:45.209
and then get all those front tables served

05:45.375 --> 05:46.500
before they start singing.

05:46.675 --> 05:48.010
- Got it.
- What'd I just say?

05:49.296 --> 05:51.034
(Giggles) I'm just amazed, okay?

05:51.201 --> 05:52.945
I mean, look at us. We're at the Bluebird.

05:53.336 --> 05:55.198
We used to dream about this place.

05:55.396 --> 05:57.011
I know, but I also know

05:57.172 --> 05:58.148
that if you don't remember all this stuff,

05:58.326 --> 05:59.825
you're gonna end up on
the first bus back home

06:00.539 --> 06:03.448
with me by your side because
I gave notice too early.

06:04.243 --> 06:07.280
You got a signed record deal.
Rayna's gonna be just fine.

06:07.767 --> 06:09.736
You move here just to
tell me what I wanna hear?

06:09.921 --> 06:11.985
Apparently I moved here so
you'd have a sofa to sleep on.

06:12.300 --> 06:13.135
(Whispers) Thank you.

06:13.310 --> 06:14.445
(Avery, amplified voice)
Evening, everybody.

06:14.633 --> 06:17.764
Welcome to the Bluebird.
My name's Avery Barkley.

06:18.197 --> 06:19.249
(Applause, piano playing)

06:20.358 --> 06:21.843
♪

06:24.937 --> 06:27.153
♪ First you fall

06:28.532 --> 06:30.891
♪ And then you fly

06:32.780 --> 06:35.971
♪ And you believe that you belong ♪

06:36.182 --> 06:38.258
♪ Up in the sky

06:39.970 --> 06:42.157
♪ Flap your arms

06:43.990 --> 06:45.906
♪ As you run

06:48.659 --> 06:52.208
♪ Every revolution brings you

06:52.575 --> 06:55.160
♪ Closer to the sun

06:56.142 --> 06:59.235
♪ You fall asleep in motion

06:59.555 --> 07:02.741
♪ In uncharted hemispheres

07:03.413 --> 07:06.241
♪ And you wake up with the stars... ♪

07:06.807 --> 07:08.417
I always loved that one.

07:08.849 --> 07:10.384
Him or the song?

07:10.894 --> 07:12.546
There's no talking during performances.

07:12.776 --> 07:14.506
I'm just saying, I can't
remember the last time

07:14.709 --> 07:16.281
you didn't have a boyfriend.

07:17.058 --> 07:19.764
Yeah, I know. It's part of the problem.

07:20.818 --> 07:21.861
Got to learn to stand on my own.

07:22.067 --> 07:24.824
♪ That's how you learn to live alone ♪

07:25.016 --> 07:26.412
Man, I'm not sure about this paint.

07:26.686 --> 07:27.401
What are you talking about?

07:27.597 --> 07:30.211
It's way better than the girly
pastels Scarlett had goin'.

07:30.490 --> 07:31.555
(Paint can clatters)

07:31.752 --> 07:32.880
(Sighs) Although I do like this couch.

07:33.078 --> 07:34.336
That was nice of her to leave it.

07:34.538 --> 07:36.262
Well, it's just till she
finds a place of her own.

07:36.424 --> 07:38.279
- When's that gonna be?
- I don't know, Will.

07:38.579 --> 07:41.220
We're not exactly talking
every day since she said "no".

07:41.709 --> 07:43.177
(Bart crow's "busted" playing)

07:45.024 --> 07:46.111
♪ You're always running

07:46.267 --> 07:47.595
yeah, you're right.

07:47.821 --> 07:49.893
- Needs somethin'.
Whoo-hoo! - What...

07:50.144 --> 07:51.796
All right! Come on.

07:51.985 --> 07:53.029
Hook 'em horns!

07:53.251 --> 07:54.594
Quit foolin' around, man. Wha...

07:54.799 --> 07:56.091
I'm not foolin' around. That's
perfect. (Paintbrush clatters)

07:56.321 --> 07:57.855
All right, would you just stop? Just stop.

07:58.036 --> 07:58.979
Stop what? What?

08:00.448 --> 08:01.958
I mean, do you even
listen to country music?

08:02.169 --> 08:04.263
- What's that supposed to mean?
- "Friends in low places"

08:04.455 --> 08:06.525
"Brand new girlfriend",
"How do you like me now"...

08:06.772 --> 08:08.864
<i>That's how you deal with a breakup, man.</i>

08:09.056 --> 08:13.177
You get drunk. You get
loud! You get... busy.

08:14.904 --> 08:16.317
(Cell phone beeps) What are you doin'?

08:16.631 --> 08:17.356
I'm just making an appointment

08:17.595 --> 08:19.357
- to get the stick out of your ass.
- Oh, you're hilarious.

08:19.550 --> 08:21.380
Hey, hey, Laycee, yeah.
Gunnar and me are having

08:21.579 --> 08:24.467
- a housewarming party tomorrow.
- The paint won't even be dry...

08:24.667 --> 08:26.191
Yes, yes, bring 'em. Bring 'em all.

08:26.397 --> 08:28.156
No. The more, the merrier. Yeah.

08:28.385 --> 08:29.626
(Whispers) You're welcome, by the way.

08:29.854 --> 08:31.085
(Sighs and whispers) Thank you.

08:31.242 --> 08:32.652
(Chuckles)

08:36.062 --> 08:37.924
(Sheets rustling)

08:40.683 --> 08:42.794
Okay, stop. Stop.

08:45.423 --> 08:48.647
(Sighs) So this mean I don't get the job?

08:49.968 --> 08:51.203
I'll let you know.

08:51.850 --> 08:53.116
Because I can try again.

08:53.426 --> 08:54.844
- Get home safe. (Remote control clicks)
- Okay.

08:55.032 --> 08:56.480
<i>(Man) Fans across the world are monitoring</i>

08:56.687 --> 08:58.317
<i>the superstar's condition closely..</i>

08:58.524 --> 09:00.087
<i>A role in which social media</i>

09:00.317 --> 09:02.289
<i>seems to be playing a huge part.</i>

09:02.644 --> 09:04.607
<i>But while concern for the
singer's uncertain future</i>

09:04.800 --> 09:06.415
<i>is trending worldwide,</i>

09:06.866 --> 09:09.870
<i>fans have been drawn here to Nashville,
along with... (Dials cell phone)</i>

09:10.162 --> 09:12.707
Glenn? Get me a thousand candles.

09:14.342 --> 09:15.467
I need to pray.

09:15.781 --> 09:17.413
(Buzzer)

09:18.641 --> 09:20.582
So you're the drunk who
was driving Rayna Jaymes.

09:21.036 --> 09:22.636
You know, she got a lot of fans in here.

09:25.461 --> 09:27.151
Better hope she pulls through.

09:30.223 --> 09:32.269
(Door clanks loudly)

09:32.813 --> 09:34.499
♪

09:34.780 --> 09:45.068
Synced and corrected by
Nantinha ~ www.addic7ed.com ~

09:47.657 --> 09:49.792
♪

09:50.789 --> 09:51.505
(Juliette) All right, guys,

09:51.739 --> 09:52.627
we're gonna go through the set list

09:52.838 --> 09:54.729
plus an additional song
that I added for tonight.

09:54.935 --> 09:56.371
We haven't done it before, so...

09:56.581 --> 09:58.583
You serious? I mean, do we even know it?

09:58.782 --> 10:00.675
Oh, you know it. It's a classic.

10:00.887 --> 10:02.560
(Indistinct conversations)

10:02.766 --> 10:03.874
(Feedback crackles)

10:04.084 --> 10:05.394
- Hey.
- Hey.

10:06.567 --> 10:07.972
You, uh, come to see me play, or...

10:08.204 --> 10:10.982
Oh. I would if I could, but I really wanted

10:11.180 --> 10:13.371
to talk to Miss Barnes
if you've got a minute.

10:13.560 --> 10:15.030
Yeah, only if you call me "Juliette".

10:15.205 --> 10:17.003
We did plan a birthday party together once.

10:17.245 --> 10:20.367
That was a really sweet thing
you did for Deacon. Um...

10:20.609 --> 10:21.950
So I was wonderin'

10:22.376 --> 10:23.712
if you would be kind enough

10:24.243 --> 10:25.949
to consider helping me help him.

10:26.165 --> 10:27.365
I got an advance on my record deal

10:27.603 --> 10:29.740
and a little bit of money
from my mama for his bail.

10:29.964 --> 10:33.204
It would be a loan, and I
would pay you back every penny,

10:33.769 --> 10:35.649
but I don't think he
deserves to be in jail.

10:36.538 --> 10:39.281
Let him got all right? Addicts are addicts.

10:39.477 --> 10:41.635
You will spend all your time
and energy trying to save him,

10:41.828 --> 10:43.548
and the only thanks
you're gonna get in return

10:44.069 --> 10:46.104
is a broken heart when
he disappoints you again,

10:46.288 --> 10:47.362
'cause he will.

10:49.758 --> 10:51.355
Sorry I bothered you.

10:54.469 --> 10:55.651
(Footsteps retreat)

10:56.103 --> 10:57.397
All right, y'all, let's go.

10:57.671 --> 10:59.709
I have no idea who all these people are.

11:00.014 --> 11:01.505
It's a party, man. Who cares?

11:01.729 --> 11:03.928
There's someone I want you
to meet, though. Hey, Laycee!

11:04.251 --> 11:05.577
This is my roomie, Gunnar.

11:05.777 --> 11:07.241
-Hi.
- Hey, how you doin'?

11:07.479 --> 11:09.122
- This is my friend Savannah.
- Hey.

11:09.338 --> 11:10.324
- Hi.
- What's up, baby? Mmm.

11:10.589 --> 11:12.084
Is he the one you were telling us about?

11:12.310 --> 11:13.815
Don't you believe a word out of his mouth.

11:14.049 --> 11:17.309
So you're not "the best damn
songwriter in Nashville"?

11:17.844 --> 11:20.515
<i>The best? Top ten, maybe.</i>

11:20.817 --> 11:22.081
Come on. Write us a song.

11:22.243 --> 11:23.383
Yeah, it doesn't really work like that.

11:23.567 --> 11:25.431
You kind of have to be, uh, inspired.

11:25.925 --> 11:28.752
Oh, I bet I can inspire
you to do a lot of things.

11:29.344 --> 11:30.931
(People cheering and speaking indistinctly)

11:31.667 --> 11:32.786
(Man) Here you go.

11:34.732 --> 11:35.989
(Laughter) Whoo!

11:36.874 --> 11:39.580
Hey, Laycee, uh, let's
go get some fresh air.

11:44.708 --> 11:47.143
Well, I'm assuming you called me
here because you've made a decision.

11:47.335 --> 11:50.775
Look, I know it'd be better for you
if I just took care of things, but...

11:50.991 --> 11:52.231
So you've confirmed it?

11:52.437 --> 11:53.980
With three home pregnancy tests.

11:54.301 --> 11:56.929
I have an appointment to find out
how far along I am if you wanna come.

11:57.119 --> 11:58.629
I already have a family, Peggy.

12:00.716 --> 12:01.856
I'm sorry.

12:02.502 --> 12:04.601
All this is more than I
can deal with right now.

12:04.964 --> 12:06.566
Just tell me what you want from me.

12:07.716 --> 12:09.970
I remember you telling
me that having children

12:11.601 --> 12:13.186
opened up a space in your heart

12:13.389 --> 12:15.041
you never knew existed.

12:15.697 --> 12:17.382
I wanna feel that, Teddy.

12:19.104 --> 12:20.985
I can offer you financial support,

12:21.474 --> 12:22.889
but that's it.

12:26.003 --> 12:26.993
<i>(Woman on TV) ... That he, in fact,</i>

12:27.262 --> 12:28.590
<i>has Parkinson's disease.</i>

12:28.786 --> 12:30.036
(Tandy) Hey.

12:30.264 --> 12:31.735
(Sighs)

12:33.253 --> 12:34.684
I thought no one would be here.

12:34.891 --> 12:37.307
- Happy to see you, too, daddy.
- That's not what I meant.

12:37.524 --> 12:39.594
I just thought you wouldn't
be coming in till later,

12:39.809 --> 12:42.301
and I didn't wanna... I
didn't wanna leave her alone.

12:42.738 --> 12:44.123
Teddy and the girls are on their way.

12:45.920 --> 12:46.990
(Sighs) I don't think that means

12:47.214 --> 12:48.472
<i>- that you have to leave.
- A wall of cards,</i>

12:48.750 --> 12:50.932
<i>flowers, and Teddy bears has grown</i>

12:51.163 --> 12:52.720
<i>outside Vanderbilt hospital.</i>

12:52.907 --> 12:54.816
<i>It's here where country music great</i>

12:54.985 --> 12:57.383
<i>Rayna Jaymes remains in critical condition,</i>

12:57.592 --> 13:00.000
<i>leaving many of her
fans afraid that history</i>

13:00.198 --> 13:01.528
<i>may be repeating itself.</i>

13:01.762 --> 13:03.061
<i>In a tragic coincidence,</i>

13:03.386 --> 13:06.825
<i>her own mother, Virginia
Wyatt, died in a fiery crash</i>

13:07.072 --> 13:08.710
<i>when the singer was
only 12... (Turns off TV)</i>

13:09.070 --> 13:11.780
(Monitor beeping steadily,
remote control clatters)

13:12.080 --> 13:13.794
I wasn't there for your mother.

13:14.318 --> 13:16.451
I wasn't at her bedside.

13:16.724 --> 13:18.442
Maybe it would have made a difference.

13:18.664 --> 13:20.799
It's not your fault
that you were out of town

13:21.275 --> 13:22.601
when it happened.

13:23.517 --> 13:25.280
But you're here now.

13:26.124 --> 13:27.599
So talk to her.

13:27.899 --> 13:29.433
Just tell her that.

13:29.950 --> 13:31.618
(Ventilator whooshing)

13:32.223 --> 13:33.748
(Footsteps retreat)

13:41.069 --> 13:42.436
(Lowered voice) Forgive me, darling,

13:43.195 --> 13:44.583
for everything.

13:45.656 --> 13:47.046
<i>(Deacon) I know I screwed up.</i>

13:47.290 --> 13:49.950
And I know you've been
seeing Teddy Conrad, but...

13:50.254 --> 13:54.413
I don't want you to
anymore. I love you, Ray.

13:54.612 --> 13:57.213
I love you more than anything
else in the whole world.

13:57.522 --> 14:00.582
Let's do this, baby, please. Marry me.

14:05.550 --> 14:07.901
-I love you so much.
- (Whispers) I love you, too.

