My name is Megan Vannoy. I'm
your court-appointed attorney.

14:27.520 --> 14:28.901
Here's where you stand legally.

14:29.095 --> 14:31.371
The D.A. Wants to postpone
trial for as long as possible

14:31.578 --> 14:34.130
in the event they're able to
upgrade to involuntary manslaughter.

14:34.655 --> 14:36.268
You mean if Rayna dies.

14:36.663 --> 14:38.749
Carries a sentence of 10 to 30 years.

14:39.548 --> 14:41.010
She gonna die?

14:42.161 --> 14:43.680
Could go either way.

14:44.859 --> 14:46.941
(Opens folder) Why don't
you tell me what happened?

14:47.710 --> 14:49.210
I was drunk.

14:50.117 --> 14:52.061
We crashed. My fault.

14:52.447 --> 14:53.535
Not much of a defense.

14:53.745 --> 14:56.701
I don't know what you're trying
to dig up or sniff out, but...

14:57.834 --> 15:00.079
You're starting to piss me off, so...

15:01.617 --> 15:03.650
I'd like to go back to my cell.

15:03.868 --> 15:05.054
(Chair scrapes floor)

15:05.252 --> 15:06.822
Well, I'm pretty good at what I do,

15:07.132 --> 15:08.927
so don't get too comfortable.

15:09.151 --> 15:11.810
Do us both a favor. Don't waste your time.

15:16.664 --> 15:17.937
(Woman) Okay, doctor,
her vitals are stable.

15:18.260 --> 15:20.215
- Let's half her dose on the propofol, okay?
- Okay.

15:20.646 --> 15:21.829
(Ventilator whooshing)

15:22.008 --> 15:24.477
- Rayna, can you hear me?
- Okay, we're holding sedation.

15:24.676 --> 15:26.288
We're lowering your sedation level so
we can perform some cognitive tests.

15:26.441 --> 15:27.838
Hey. What's going on?

15:28.218 --> 15:29.492
Um, they're bringing her
out for a few minutes,

15:29.690 --> 15:31.393
but I didn't realize that
they're running some tests,

15:31.597 --> 15:32.491
so I don't know if it's a good time

15:32.669 --> 15:34.394
- for the girls to be here.
- No, I wanna see.

15:34.627 --> 15:36.456
(Teddy) No, your aunt's right.
Come on, girls. Let's go.

15:36.715 --> 15:38.186
(Daphne) Wait. She's waking up.

15:38.392 --> 15:40.280
Her eyes are open. (Woman)
Doctor, she's going for the tube.

15:41.003 --> 15:42.107
(Maddie) Can we go in?

15:42.322 --> 15:43.663
(Woman) Let's get
everybody out of here now.

15:43.890 --> 15:45.204
- Clear the room, please.
- Dad, what's wrong with her?

15:45.544 --> 15:47.286
(Doctor) Keep her hands down.
Let's get her back under.

15:47.547 --> 15:48.946
(Crying) Is she gonna be okay?

15:49.116 --> 15:50.262
Yeah, she will. She's fine.

15:50.439 --> 15:51.720
(Crying) No, she's not.

15:58.528 --> 15:59.871
Okay, I can turn on the sound

16:00.056 --> 16:01.661
- if you wanna hear the baby's heartbeat.
- Yes.

16:02.340 --> 16:04.917
(Ultrasound whooshing) I can
even put it on a disc for you

16:05.097 --> 16:06.774
if you wanna share it with your loved ones.

16:06.972 --> 16:08.936
That would be amazing.

16:09.165 --> 16:11.111
Have you experienced any morning sickness?

16:11.272 --> 16:14.037
I did in the beginning
a little, but not lately.

16:14.490 --> 16:17.149
Didn't stop me from
gaining weight. (Chuckles)

16:18.556 --> 16:20.361
Any cramping or bleeding?

16:20.564 --> 16:22.249
I did have a little spotting.

16:22.500 --> 16:24.275
- Which is perfectly normal.
- Yeah?

16:24.854 --> 16:26.419
Is that shadow the baby?

16:29.180 --> 16:30.886
Why aren't we hearing the heartbeat yet?

16:31.352 --> 16:34.519
(Click, whooshing stops)
I'm so sorry, Peggy.

16:34.693 --> 16:36.763
It seems you've... miscarried.

16:38.847 --> 16:40.629
(Cheers and applause)

16:44.005 --> 16:45.141
(Amplified voice) Thank you!

16:45.330 --> 16:47.385
Thank you all so, so
much for coming out here

16:47.584 --> 16:49.170
to support my album.

16:49.379 --> 16:51.059
I hope you all buy it.

16:52.205 --> 16:53.937
Before I do this next song,

16:54.211 --> 16:56.020
I wanna take a moment
to talk about somebody

16:56.708 --> 16:58.277
really important to me.

16:58.725 --> 17:02.212
That's right. Y'all, give
it up for miss Rayna Jaymes.

17:02.798 --> 17:05.252
(Cheering)

17:08.865 --> 17:12.439
I never imagined that I would
share the stage with my idol,

17:12.633 --> 17:16.247
let alone a mentor and
friend, and now she is both.

17:16.762 --> 17:18.396
(Cheers and applause) And I know tonight

17:18.647 --> 17:20.325
might be about launching my album,

17:20.619 --> 17:22.516
but without her inspiration...

17:22.724 --> 17:25.983
(Camera shutters clicking) And her
influence, I would never be here right now.

17:26.344 --> 17:29.207
(Cheers and applause)

17:29.835 --> 17:32.121
I know we all want her
to get better real quick,

17:32.310 --> 17:35.686
but until she does, I'd like
to continue her tradition,

17:35.880 --> 17:37.791
so this next song's to Rayna.

17:38.048 --> 17:40.375
I only hope I do it
half as well as she does.

