(Grunts)

20:59.002 --> 21:00.078
(Grunting)

21:00.430 --> 21:02.874
(Breathing heavily)

21:04.538 --> 21:05.724
No, man! (Slam)

21:06.595 --> 21:08.199
- You get off me! Get the hell outta here!
- What the hell?

21:08.424 --> 21:10.382
- What is your problem?
- What's going on?

21:10.574 --> 21:11.810
This creep just made a pass at me.

21:11.967 --> 21:14.406
You believe that? You get the hell out!

21:15.739 --> 21:17.242
<i>♪</i>

21:17.511 --> 21:19.984
(Indistinct conversations)

21:20.197 --> 21:21.739
Everything all right?

21:22.973 --> 21:25.783
Yeah. Yeah. About to get
all right with my girl here.

21:26.439 --> 21:28.553
Hey, you should grab yours and do the same.

21:28.733 --> 21:30.002
Come on, Laycee.

21:30.243 --> 21:32.329
<i>♪</i>

21:32.504 --> 21:35.714
Wow. Y'all, I have had so much fun tonight.

21:36.029 --> 21:37.048
I really have.

21:37.229 --> 21:37.984
But I have to say...
(Audience member whistles)

21:38.132 --> 21:40.855
- (Woman in audience) We love you!
- It's hard being so close

21:41.027 --> 21:43.178
to where Rayna's fighting for her life.

21:43.400 --> 21:44.717
And it's even harder

21:44.956 --> 21:47.269
to not be able to tell her
that I'm praying for her.

21:47.560 --> 21:49.435
So I wanna do something about that.

21:49.768 --> 21:52.314
And if any of you feel the way
that I do... (Cheers and whistles)

21:53.109 --> 21:54.840
You're welcome to join
me over at the hospital.

21:55.041 --> 21:57.321
- (Man) Yeah, we do!
- Bring your lights. Bring your love.

21:57.562 --> 22:00.614
(Cheering) Bring your
prayers for Miss Rayna Jaymes.

22:00.802 --> 22:02.244
I'll see y'all there.

22:02.449 --> 22:04.491
(Cheers and applause)

22:04.731 --> 22:05.795
Nice show tonight.

22:05.998 --> 22:07.555
Thanks. You coming?

22:07.753 --> 22:10.114
Can't. I would've, but
you kinda sprung it on us,

22:10.268 --> 22:11.920
the whole Rayna slide show thing,

22:12.099 --> 22:13.335
although interestingly enough,

22:13.510 --> 22:15.086
you were in most of the pictures.

22:15.531 --> 22:17.778
<i>Yeah. Uh-huh.</i>

22:18.073 --> 22:19.536
And what's your point?

22:19.820 --> 22:22.101
Just a friendly observation.

22:22.389 --> 22:24.773
Anyway, I'm, uh, going
to a party at the Bluebird

22:24.980 --> 22:26.445
for Scarlett's last shift.

22:26.632 --> 22:27.870
Deacon's niece.

22:28.068 --> 22:30.322
That the girl you were in love with?

22:30.889 --> 22:33.351
'Cause I might be able to save
you from a little heartbreak.

22:33.885 --> 22:35.267
From what I can tell,

22:35.477 --> 22:37.239
she's just not that into you.

22:40.023 --> 22:41.280
(Clatter)

22:42.776 --> 22:44.341
(Monitor beeping steadily,
ventilator whooshing)

22:48.620 --> 22:49.662
Hey, sweetie.

22:50.691 --> 22:51.799
How you doing?

22:52.872 --> 22:54.224
Not that good.

22:55.002 --> 22:56.304
It's so weird.

22:56.488 --> 22:59.836
He was just my Uncle
Deacon, and now he is my dad.

23:00.420 --> 23:03.284
No, he's your biological father.

23:03.832 --> 23:06.371
- I'm your dad, okay?
- Okay.

23:07.972 --> 23:09.345
He always seemed so nice,

23:09.637 --> 23:13.449
but if he loved her so
much, how could he do this?

23:13.661 --> 23:16.876
I don't know, but he did.

23:17.607 --> 23:18.568
(Slap) Hey!

23:18.976 --> 23:20.606
- God!
- You been drinking?

23:20.926 --> 23:21.809
- No, Rayna...
- Did you just wake up

23:21.955 --> 23:23.758
in the middle of the night
and just start drinkin'?

23:24.507 --> 23:27.109
Baby... I-I just
couldn't sleep last night.

23:27.264 --> 23:29.331
- No, you are just lying to me.
- No, no, no.

23:29.481 --> 23:31.013
Were you drunk last night
when you were talking to me?

23:31.155 --> 23:32.961
Sweetie... sweetie...
Get your hands off me!

23:33.128 --> 23:34.998
Where you drunk last
night when you asked me?

23:35.178 --> 23:36.410
(Exhales)

23:36.580 --> 23:38.137
When I asked you what?

23:41.437 --> 23:42.573
What, babe?

23:42.788 --> 23:44.682
Ohh.

23:45.594 --> 23:46.878
(Ring clatters)

23:47.857 --> 23:49.060
Ray? Ray!

23:49.544 --> 23:50.711
Rayna! Rayna!

23:50.856 --> 23:52.077
(Man) Go on in.

23:52.235 --> 23:53.607
(Door slams open)

23:56.268 --> 23:57.790
Thought you were gonna
tell me to go away again.

23:57.953 --> 23:59.155
I figured coming down here is the only way

23:59.329 --> 24:00.956
to get you to stop coming in.

24:01.682 --> 24:02.778
Is your hand any better?

24:02.966 --> 24:04.927
Oh, yeah, it's great. How
you doing? What's new, girl?

24:06.027 --> 24:07.830
There's nothing new. I just...

24:08.057 --> 24:10.244
I'm trying to secure your bail
and help you get outta here

24:10.579 --> 24:11.832
and help you get better.

24:11.975 --> 24:13.265
You wanna help me? I tell you what.

24:13.435 --> 24:15.530
You sell my house. Burn
the whole place down.

24:15.714 --> 24:17.548
I don't care, 'cause right
here, this is where I'm gonna be,

24:17.749 --> 24:18.696
and if Rayna doesn't pull through,

24:18.858 --> 24:19.639
- She will.
- I'm gonna be here a long...

24:19.786 --> 24:21.743
A lot of people are praying for her,
and they're praying for you, too.

24:21.919 --> 24:23.345
Well, you tell 'em to stop it, all right?

24:23.598 --> 24:25.351
<i>Listen to me. I am a drunk.</i>

24:25.530 --> 24:26.687
- That's what I am.
- You slipped.

24:26.867 --> 24:28.256
- I'm a damn drunk...
- You made a mistake.

24:28.405 --> 24:30.019
And I'm no good to you, and
I'm no good to anybody else.

24:30.186 --> 24:31.516
You are so much more than
that. You are so talented.

24:31.697 --> 24:32.940
You're so wonderful. You're like...

24:33.123 --> 24:34.357
You've been like a father to
me. You're the closest thing...

24:34.499 --> 24:36.285
What did you say to me?
What did you say to me?

24:36.489 --> 24:37.569
What?

24:37.872 --> 24:38.941
I'm not your father!

24:39.125 --> 24:40.910
<i>You understand me? I'm not your father!</i>

24:41.156 --> 24:44.090
I'm nobody's damn father! You
quit coming here. (Fist slams)

24:50.222 --> 24:52.193
I mean, he was a jerk.

24:52.403 --> 24:55.562
And I don't miss him, but you get used to

24:56.466 --> 25:00.036
having all of the sex all the time.

25:00.890 --> 25:04.448
And then all of the sudden, you don't.

25:04.934 --> 25:06.420
But you still really want it.

25:06.714 --> 25:07.880
So...

25:08.169 --> 25:10.754
Sometimes you just gotta go get it.

25:10.939 --> 25:12.034
You know what I mean?

25:12.266 --> 25:13.552
I think I know...

25:13.936 --> 25:15.729
<i>(Jeffrey James' "Bad Woman" playing)</i>

25:16.274 --> 25:18.139
(Indistinct conversations)

25:20.610 --> 25:21.709
Um...

25:21.881 --> 25:24.049
- Wait, wait. I can't.
- What's wrong, babe?

25:24.236 --> 25:27.320
Look... I just broke up with somebody, too,

25:28.291 --> 25:29.551
and this place...

25:29.847 --> 25:31.394
It's... it's all her.

25:31.830 --> 25:33.663
This couch is hers.

25:34.121 --> 25:35.974
And it's the first place that we...

25:36.189 --> 25:38.658
(Clears throat) It's just,
she's everywhere, is all.

25:38.842 --> 25:40.593
Well, you gotta get her out.

25:40.773 --> 25:42.902
How am I supposed to do that, huh?

25:43.602 --> 25:45.352
<i>♪</i>

25:45.676 --> 25:48.139
- Take it down!
- (Will) Death to the chick sofa!

25:48.549 --> 25:50.344
- Whoo-hoo-hoo!
- (Woman) Aah!

25:50.734 --> 25:52.049
(Cheering)

25:52.279 --> 25:53.204
(Flame whooshes)

25:54.317 --> 25:56.296
(Cheering and yelling)

25:56.661 --> 25:58.180
Whoo-hoo!

25:58.338 --> 25:59.082
(Whoosh)

25:59.839 --> 26:00.988
Oh, crap.

26:02.016 --> 26:03.952
(Crowd cheering)

26:04.980 --> 26:06.487
(Camera shutters clicking)

26:07.410 --> 26:08.293
(Cheering)

26:09.685 --> 26:12.768
Oh, you guys are amazing!
Oh, I love you so much!

26:12.961 --> 26:15.140
Thank y'all so much for
coming out here for Rayna.

26:15.337 --> 26:17.857
It means the world!
Thank you! God bless you!

26:18.865 --> 26:20.400
You know, they probably
won't let anyone but family

26:20.598 --> 26:21.792
into the I.C.U., right?

26:21.962 --> 26:24.586
Yeah, I know. I couldn't handle it anyway.

26:24.794 --> 26:26.313
Have the car pulled around back.

26:26.479 --> 26:29.900
Juliette? Oh, my God. You came. (gasps)

26:31.604 --> 26:33.041
Couldn't keep me away.

26:35.295 --> 26:36.963
Please don't ask me how I'm doing.

26:37.179 --> 26:38.684
I won't ask you anything.

26:39.304 --> 26:40.775
We can just sit here and not say a word

26:40.937 --> 26:42.517
if that's what you want.

26:45.427 --> 26:47.247
Did your mom ever lie to you?

26:47.425 --> 26:49.667
Pretty much every time
she opened her mouth.

26:50.546 --> 26:52.154
I would ask you what yours lied about,

26:52.368 --> 26:55.213
but I already said no questions.

26:56.768 --> 26:59.142
Sometimes I just wish there
was someone I could talk to.

26:59.822 --> 27:01.990
There really isn't anybody who understands.

27:03.780 --> 27:05.246
- Give me your phone.
- What?

27:05.434 --> 27:06.853
Come on. Let's have it.

27:07.906 --> 27:09.295
(Buttons clicking)

27:10.134 --> 27:11.955
I understand.

27:12.143 --> 27:13.276
Okay?

27:13.476 --> 27:16.326
And if you ever need
somebody to talk to, call me.

27:16.522 --> 27:17.788
You mean it?

27:17.999 --> 27:20.494
I would not give you my number if I didn't.

27:22.783 --> 27:24.690
You know this is all because of me.

27:25.705 --> 27:26.920
What's because of you?

27:27.119 --> 27:28.519
I went looking through my mom's stuff,

27:29.545 --> 27:32.982
and I found out my dad isn't really my dad.

27:34.022 --> 27:36.394
<i>So I asked Deacon if he was.</i>

27:36.692 --> 27:37.967
And what'd he say?

27:38.254 --> 27:39.924
That he didn't know.

27:40.528 --> 27:42.894
And then he got drunk
and almost killed my mom.

27:45.778 --> 27:47.225
If I hadn't been snooping...

27:47.523 --> 27:48.728
Hey, listen to me.

27:48.916 --> 27:51.201
You are not responsible for any of this.

27:51.460 --> 27:52.696
Okay?

27:54.144 --> 27:55.573
Come here.

27:57.008 --> 27:58.531
Thank you.

28:01.020 --> 28:02.561
Hey. (Sighs) There you are.

28:04.228 --> 28:05.768
Look who came to see mom.

28:08.400 --> 28:09.487
Hey, you're late.

28:09.660 --> 28:10.813
- Hi.
- People are beginning to think

28:11.014 --> 28:12.785
you were gonna miss your
own going-away party.

28:12.966 --> 28:14.157
Where you been?

28:15.236 --> 28:16.772
Went to see Deacon.

28:18.414 --> 28:20.261
- Wait. You got in?
- Yep.

28:21.552 --> 28:22.463
How is he? (Tray clatters)

28:23.329 --> 28:24.819
(Voice breaking) He's not great.

28:25.170 --> 28:26.770
And now how are you? (Clatter)

28:27.722 --> 28:29.611
- Fine.
- You're not fine.

28:29.794 --> 28:31.401
I've known you since the first grade.

28:32.074 --> 28:33.780
What in the world did he say to you?

28:33.974 --> 28:36.297
(Crying) What if everybody
else is right about him...

28:37.538 --> 28:39.119
And I'm wrong?

28:39.500 --> 28:42.349
Look, tonight's not about your uncle, okay?

28:42.537 --> 28:44.937
Tonight is about you and
the fact that your friends

28:45.099 --> 28:46.474
wanna celebrate your having worked here

28:46.671 --> 28:48.128
and going off with a record deal.

28:48.465 --> 28:50.924
So turn that junk off and
let's get through this shift

28:51.287 --> 28:53.682
so we can close up and have us a party.

28:54.123 --> 28:55.430
Okay.

28:55.741 --> 28:57.490
(Whispers) Okay.

28:57.792 --> 28:59.675
I'm glad you're here. (Crying)

29:00.060 --> 29:03.221
(Monitor beeping steadily,
ventilator whooshing)

29:07.868 --> 29:10.235
It's okay. You can come closer.

29:15.078 --> 29:17.603
I just keep waiting for
her to open her eyes,

29:17.836 --> 29:19.196
but she never does.

29:21.747 --> 29:23.157
I bet you miss her.

29:24.947 --> 29:26.485
Your mom.

29:28.120 --> 29:29.132
When she was good,

29:29.310 --> 29:31.073
she'd play your mama's music,

29:31.377 --> 29:32.774
and we'd just lay there on the floor

29:32.963 --> 29:35.699
and listen to those songs
over and over and over again.

29:38.945 --> 29:40.763
You know what her favorite one was?

29:40.942 --> 29:42.944
"This love ain't big enough."

29:44.011 --> 29:46.058
She always said I was her platinum baby

29:46.291 --> 29:48.437
'cause that came out the year I was born.

29:48.606 --> 29:49.969
<i>(Rayna) Well, he's here. Thank God.</i>

29:50.135 --> 29:52.590
Right, and so now we
know he bailed on rehab,

29:52.785 --> 29:54.280
made it home safe and sound.

29:54.469 --> 29:56.490
- Let's go.
- I know, but I need to talk to him.

29:56.670 --> 29:59.021
What you need is to just let him go.

29:59.706 --> 30:00.544
Come on.

30:00.773 --> 30:03.734
(Voice breaks) I mean, I'm
pregnant. It's probably his.

30:03.955 --> 30:05.931
I need to just... I need
to at least talk to him.

30:06.129 --> 30:07.365
(Bottles clatter)

30:07.620 --> 30:10.032
He needs help, you know?
And he's... he's sick.

30:10.244 --> 30:11.672
Well, fine, and you've tried to help him,

30:11.853 --> 30:13.298
but you cannot help somebody

30:13.487 --> 30:15.730
who doesn't want to help himself. (Thud)

30:16.053 --> 30:17.301
You want him to be the father?

30:17.472 --> 30:18.754
Do you have any idea
what could happen to you

30:18.933 --> 30:20.707
<i>or to that baby if he was?</i>

30:23.072 --> 30:24.318
(Buzzer, door opens)

30:25.078 --> 30:27.048
- Thought I made myself clear...
- Single vehicle accident

30:27.266 --> 30:28.558
involving the male owner
of a car (Door closes)

30:28.719 --> 30:30.126
With two prior D.U.I.s

30:30.341 --> 30:32.838
and a blood alcohol level of
over twice the legal limit.

30:33.067 --> 30:34.846
The female occupant had zero.

30:35.044 --> 30:36.948
When the police ask who was
responsible for the crash,

30:37.150 --> 30:39.812
not surprisingly, the
car's owner said it was him.

30:40.011 --> 30:41.632
Yeah, I was there... And with
no reason to disbelieve you,

30:41.819 --> 30:43.260
- the police stopped investigating.
- It's kinda late.

30:43.458 --> 30:46.415
Don't you have a husband or, like,
kids to get home to or something?

30:46.882 --> 30:47.913
(Chair scrapes floor)

30:48.106 --> 30:49.135
I found a hospital report

30:49.306 --> 30:50.751
that references diagonal bruising

30:50.918 --> 30:52.379
across Ms. Jaymes' abdomen,

30:52.608 --> 30:54.808
2 inches wide from upper
left to bottom right.

30:55.206 --> 30:57.301
<i>She was the one behind the wheel.</i>

30:58.197 --> 31:00.309
If I hadn't been drinking,
none of it would've happened.

31:00.479 --> 31:01.316
Did your reckless actions

31:01.523 --> 31:03.805
contribute to a tragic accident? Probably.

31:04.966 --> 31:07.662
Did you commit a crime? No.

31:19.357 --> 31:20.462
Good party.

31:20.744 --> 31:22.344
Ended a little sooner
than I thought it would.

31:22.501 --> 31:23.904
I'm an idiot. You know that?

31:24.117 --> 31:26.371
Well... Burning the furniture

31:26.534 --> 31:28.127
might not have been the
smartest thing to do.

31:28.309 --> 31:29.577
Uh, you're an idiot, too.

31:29.744 --> 31:31.561
Oh, hang on there, man.
I was just trying to help.

31:31.728 --> 31:32.962
I can't do this, man.

31:33.673 --> 31:35.903
I can't do it. I can't
"party" my feelings away,

31:36.226 --> 31:37.818
and I can't go around
screwing random girls.

31:37.986 --> 31:39.091
I'm not like you.

31:39.268 --> 31:40.952
I can't pretend I'm
feeling something I'm not.

31:41.794 --> 31:43.683
Look, I'm not judging you
for staying in the closet...

31:43.852 --> 31:46.501
Whoa. Hey, hey, hey. I'm not
in any damn closet, all right?

31:46.746 --> 31:48.228
Get that through your skull.

31:48.732 --> 31:50.170
(Man speaking indistinctly)

31:50.404 --> 31:52.315
Okay. I guess it's just me

31:52.482 --> 31:54.171
who's been avoiding my feelings then.

31:55.624 --> 31:57.711
(Huffs) I'm going to the Bluebird, man.

31:58.433 --> 32:01.215
They're having a party that
actually celebrates somethin'.

32:02.763 --> 32:04.965
(Cheers and whistles) (Giggles)

32:05.248 --> 32:06.676
(Cheering)

32:06.940 --> 32:08.467
Oh, I'm gonna miss you guys so much.

32:08.646 --> 32:10.046
I think I'm even gonna miss this thing.

32:10.207 --> 32:13.065
- Let's toast... to Scarlett.
- (All) To Scarlett!

32:13.239 --> 32:15.252
Thank you. Um, just let
me... Let me go hang this up.

32:15.522 --> 32:16.908
Keep drinking. (Laughter)

32:17.190 --> 32:18.548
<i>(Leagues' "You Belong Here" playing)</i>

32:21.520 --> 32:22.499
Hi.

32:26.580 --> 32:27.700
Been a while.

32:27.868 --> 32:29.923
Yeah. I guess we've
been on different shifts.

32:30.151 --> 32:31.928
Kinda on purpose on my part.

32:32.701 --> 32:33.746
Well, you look nice.

32:34.246 --> 32:35.139
Um...

32:35.591 --> 32:37.022
(Sniffs) Did you come from a barbecue?

32:38.216 --> 32:39.573
Uh, somethin' like that.

32:40.565 --> 32:41.580
Look...

32:41.862 --> 32:43.270
<i>♪ You belong here</i>

32:43.834 --> 32:46.445
I know why you said "no."

32:46.951 --> 32:48.623
<i>♪ We've been waiting so long</i>

32:48.889 --> 32:50.552
I gotta grow up sometime, right?

32:51.373 --> 32:53.175
<i>♪ You belong here</i>

32:54.030 --> 32:55.733
But unless you have any objections,

32:56.272 --> 32:58.376
I'd like to join the festivities.

32:59.818 --> 33:02.144
I mean, we were co-workers first, right?

33:02.314 --> 33:03.880
Yeah, of course.

33:04.523 --> 33:05.706
Oh.

33:06.014 --> 33:09.280
Sorry. They're just, uh,
asking for you out here.

33:09.591 --> 33:11.486
Everybody wants you to do a song.

33:11.694 --> 33:13.406
Oh, okay. Thank you. Um...

33:14.333 --> 33:15.573
See you out there.

33:15.887 --> 33:21.304
<i>♪ Let it all begin, you'd
be a fool to fight it ♪</i>

33:21.455 --> 33:23.362
Can't take "no" for an answer, huh?

33:24.137 --> 33:25.963
Guessin' that makes two of us.

33:27.370 --> 33:29.023
(Applause, woman shouts indistinctly)

33:29.185 --> 33:30.345
(Amplified voice) I don't really
know what y'all wanna hear.

33:30.506 --> 33:32.168
(Man) How about "Looking
For a Place to Shine"?

33:32.376 --> 33:33.366
I could do that,

33:33.555 --> 33:36.266
but what occurs to me is, um,

33:36.478 --> 33:38.253
I'm leaving this place because

33:38.518 --> 33:40.061
I've been signed by Rayna Jaymes.

33:40.273 --> 33:41.677
May all of our prayers be with her.

33:42.291 --> 33:44.233
And I-I wouldn't be signed anywhere

33:44.471 --> 33:47.066
or be singing anywhere, even,

33:47.290 --> 33:49.534
without the influence
of somebody in this room.

33:50.003 --> 33:53.015
And I wondered if they would
come up and sing with me.

33:53.340 --> 33:55.528
Um, it's a song we wrote not very long ago.

33:55.745 --> 33:58.119
It's called "Why Can't I Say Goodnight."

33:58.418 --> 34:00.150
Gunnar, would you sing with me?

34:00.493 --> 34:02.302
(Scarlett chuckles) (Cheers and applause)

34:02.530 --> 34:03.912
(Man) Whoo! Whoo!

34:04.143 --> 34:05.384
(Man) Yeah, sing it, Scarlett!

34:05.559 --> 34:06.813
(Applause continues) (Man) Whoo! Whoo!

34:07.033 --> 34:08.338
(Woman shouts indistinctly)

34:08.617 --> 34:10.465
(Guitar playing)

34:11.449 --> 34:13.076
♪

34:16.824 --> 34:20.399
(Both) ♪ It's almost sunrise

34:21.630 --> 34:26.347
♪ Hours and hours gone by

34:29.074 --> 34:32.534
♪ Candles are burned down

34:34.101 --> 34:38.601
♪ Turned into morning light

34:40.828 --> 34:46.050
♪ The time to go has come and gone ♪

34:46.292 --> 34:51.109
♪ Why can't I

34:52.382 --> 34:53.888
♪ Why

34:54.246 --> 34:56.047
♪ Can't I

34:56.214 --> 34:58.850
♪ Say goodnight?

35:00.834 --> 35:04.691
♪ The whole world is sleeping

35:06.098 --> 35:10.307
♪ And still I can't give in

35:13.408 --> 35:16.764
♪ It's a love story

35:18.106 --> 35:19.338
You should, uh...

35:20.588 --> 35:22.323
Probably just get on home.

35:23.428 --> 35:25.255
I'm not much in the mood tonight.

35:25.484 --> 35:27.507
♪ The time to go

35:27.773 --> 35:30.394
♪ Has come and gone

35:30.611 --> 35:32.844
♪ Why can't I...

35:33.056 --> 35:34.275
Hey, I got your message.

35:37.561 --> 35:39.215
Something wrong?

35:40.533 --> 35:41.431
♪ Can't I say...

35:41.602 --> 35:43.443
I heard the baby's heartbeat.

35:47.618 --> 35:51.436
♪ I'm using up all my strength

35:52.495 --> 35:56.436
♪ I can't tear myself away

35:57.487 --> 36:00.933
♪ It only gets harder as

36:02.007 --> 36:05.360
♪ Night turns to day

36:05.660 --> 36:07.347
<i>Hey, it's Scarlett. Leave a message.</i>

36:07.683 --> 36:11.323
Scarlett, hey. It's, uh, Juliette Barnes.

36:12.490 --> 36:16.503
(Exhaling) ♪ Honey, that I'd rather be

36:19.073 --> 36:23.477
(Exhales) ♪ Than right here in your arms

36:24.651 --> 36:29.048
♪ With your head lyin' on me

36:29.250 --> 36:30.488
(Exhaling)

36:31.430 --> 36:36.524
♪ The time to go has come and gone ♪

36:36.788 --> 36:41.726
♪ Why can't I

36:42.931 --> 36:44.357
♪ Why

36:44.689 --> 36:47.595
♪ Can't I say

36:47.785 --> 36:49.935
♪ Goodnight?

36:50.520 --> 36:52.378
(Song ends)

36:52.997 --> 36:54.560
(Cheers and applause)

36:54.775 --> 36:55.742
- Thank you.
- (Gunnar) Thank you.

36:55.936 --> 36:56.879
(Cheering)

36:58.104 --> 37:00.342
- Thanks.
- Thank you for singing with me.

37:00.545 --> 37:02.834
(Sighs) To be honest,
I didn't really want to.

37:03.806 --> 37:04.961
Why did you, then?

37:05.889 --> 37:07.988
You don't give up on people you love.

37:15.916 --> 37:16.867
(Man) Nice job, Gunnar.

37:22.887 --> 37:24.397
(Monitor beeping steadily,
door slides closed)

37:25.435 --> 37:27.593
(Ventilator whooshing)

37:28.075 --> 37:29.980
We make our choices, don't we?

37:30.250 --> 37:33.402
Passion over stability,
fireworks over family.

37:33.564 --> 37:34.285
Excuse me?

37:34.497 --> 37:36.907
I just wish you'd tried harder, Teddy...

37:37.133 --> 37:39.111
Loved her a little more, found some way

37:39.268 --> 37:40.812
to keep her happy, keep her at home,

37:40.977 --> 37:43.791
keep her from being
drawn to a man like him.

37:43.932 --> 37:45.132
I'm sorry, but please don't stand here

37:45.287 --> 37:46.834
and project your crap onto me.

37:47.040 --> 37:49.003
I did everything I could
to keep Rayna happy,

37:49.221 --> 37:50.821
and she was happy for a long time,

37:51.017 --> 37:52.271
but I saw the writing on the wall,

37:52.464 --> 37:54.247
and I didn't wait for
my wife to pack her bags

37:54.413 --> 37:55.861
and abandon me like yours did.

37:56.086 --> 37:57.656
She didn't. She died in an accident.

37:57.888 --> 37:59.244
(Monitor beeping erratically)

38:01.224 --> 38:03.608
- Nurse? We need some help in here.
- (Teddy) What's happening?

38:03.779 --> 38:05.320
Blood pressure and brain
activity are spiking.

38:05.482 --> 38:06.513
I'll get the doctor.

38:06.705 --> 38:08.150
All right, check that
airway. Make sure it's clear.

38:08.329 --> 38:09.968
<i>- Let's get some...
- (Deacon) I don't believe in the program.</i>

38:10.127 --> 38:11.752
<i>(Deacon and Rayna arguing indistinctly)</i>

38:12.322 --> 38:14.250
<i>This is who I am!</i>

38:14.464 --> 38:15.615
<i>(Arguing continues)</i>

38:17.468 --> 38:19.099
<i>Stop it. Give me that.</i>

38:19.383 --> 38:20.949
<i>(Tires screech)</i>

38:30.279 --> 38:31.702
(Doctor) It's not uncommon
for patients to react

38:31.876 --> 38:33.834
to what they're
experiencing subconsciously.

38:34.243 --> 38:35.331
There were no seizures.

38:35.559 --> 38:36.763
In fact, her intracranial pressure

38:36.938 --> 38:38.190
has subsided significantly.

38:38.386 --> 38:40.128
Swelling's gone down.
Blood flow looks good,

38:40.416 --> 38:41.487
as does her E.E.G.

38:41.676 --> 38:42.672
So we're comfortable bringing her

38:42.841 --> 38:44.098
out of the induced coma at this point,

38:44.281 --> 38:45.680
though she'll still need time to recover.

38:45.843 --> 38:47.441
Can the family be present for that?

38:47.607 --> 38:49.580
They can be, but they should
be prepared for any outcome.

38:50.706 --> 38:52.304
Wait. Uh, meaning what?

38:52.849 --> 38:54.096
There's no way for us to know yet

38:54.276 --> 38:56.539
if there's been any impact
on her cognitive abilities.

38:56.731 --> 38:59.037
Are you saying that she's
not gonna recognize us?

38:59.238 --> 39:01.003
She might not recognize anything.

39:01.441 --> 39:02.547
(Door creaks)

39:08.651 --> 39:09.877
(Car door closes, alarm chirps)

39:10.506 --> 39:11.815
(Dog barking in distance)

39:16.658 --> 39:17.955
You moving in?

39:18.171 --> 39:19.349
Yeah.

39:20.839 --> 39:22.368
Did you post his bail?

39:23.115 --> 39:25.140
My people are working on it right now.

39:26.066 --> 39:27.195
Thank you.

39:29.106 --> 39:31.983
Man, Deacon really fell off
the wagon hard, didn't he?

39:32.173 --> 39:33.474
Yeah, he did.

39:33.681 --> 39:35.101
Wish I knew why.

39:38.650 --> 39:40.312
(Doctor) Okay, Rayna,
you're doing just great.

39:40.498 --> 39:42.591
Stay with us. We're almost
done, okay? (Velcro rips)

39:42.850 --> 39:44.398
We're gonna get some of
this stuff off of you.

39:45.499 --> 39:47.276
Thank you. All right, Rayna,

39:47.483 --> 39:48.850
we're gonna take the tube out now,

39:49.184 --> 39:50.326
so what I need you to do

39:50.686 --> 39:53.416
is take a deep breath
and then cough. (Coughs)

39:54.046 --> 39:55.753
(Rayna gags) Very good.

39:57.156 --> 39:59.857
Rayna, you're at Vanderbilt hospital.

40:00.083 --> 40:01.694
Do you understand that? If you do,

40:02.063 --> 40:04.533
blink twice. Now don't try and talk.

40:12.708 --> 40:16.372
All right, now do you know who
the people in the hallway are?

40:30.989 --> 40:32.137
They can come in.

40:32.348 --> 40:33.713
(Exhales)

40:41.823 --> 40:43.031
(Crying)

40:49.094 --> 40:50.112
(Buzzer)

40:50.314 --> 40:51.902
(Door rumbles)

40:52.055 --> 40:52.953
What?

40:58.318 --> 40:59.400
(Sighs heavily)

40:59.679 --> 41:00.996
You're being released.

41:02.507 --> 41:03.901
What, somebody post my bail?

41:04.060 --> 41:06.877
No. Someone confirmed you weren't driving.

41:07.058 --> 41:08.885
(Scoffs) Who did that?

41:09.037 --> 41:10.473
Rayna.

41:11.673 --> 41:13.140
She's conscious.

41:15.495 --> 41:16.955
I'll give you a minute.

41:19.893 --> 41:20.939
(Exhaling)

41:25.737 --> 41:27.348
(Exhales deeply)

41:28.202 --> 41:29.080
(Man) Tandy Hampton?

41:29.233 --> 41:30.894
- Yes?
- Justin Ramer, U.S. attorney's office.

41:31.074 --> 41:35.133
Oh, you people really
need to stop harassing me.

41:35.582 --> 41:37.121
I already told your boss I'm not interested

41:37.511 --> 41:40.494
in helping make any sort
of case against my father.

41:40.955 --> 41:43.594
And if any of this information
is coming from Teddy Conrad,

41:43.900 --> 41:46.091
you should seriously consider the source.

41:46.262 --> 41:48.233
Before you go all in
to protect your father,

41:48.413 --> 41:49.461
you should know this.

41:49.630 --> 41:51.275
There's evidence to support his involvement

41:51.450 --> 41:52.768
with your mother's death.

41:53.631 --> 41:57.068
- What?
- That car accident was no accident.

41:57.761 --> 41:59.053
Well, that's ridiculous.

41:59.237 --> 42:01.646
You know your father. You
know what he's capable of.

42:02.037 --> 42:04.125
You just assumed your family was immune.

42:08.451 --> 42:11.331
The nurse told I'd find you here.

42:12.103 --> 42:14.459
Yeah, I've been coming
out here as much as I can.

42:14.710 --> 42:16.964
Breathe this fresh air, take in this view.

42:17.144 --> 42:19.116
- Well, it's sure a
good one. - Mm-hmm.

42:19.286 --> 42:21.451
Probably not worth being
in the hospital for.

42:21.661 --> 42:24.310
(Chuckles) True that.

42:25.740 --> 42:27.899
He never was any good for you, you know?

42:28.582 --> 42:30.741
- Deacon.
- Yeah, I know who you're talking about.

42:31.348 --> 42:32.840
I'm just...

